The paper discusses the integration of multimedia annotations and Linked Data principles, which are relevant to the fields of web development (cs.WEB), information retrieval (cs.IR), digital libraries (cs.DL), semantic web (cs.SI), and multimedia (cs.MM). The Open Annotation Collaboration (OAC) model is specifically focused on interoperability specifications for annotations, which is relevant to all of these sub-categories. However, since the paper emphasizes the use of common web standards and the exchange of annotations, cs.WEB is the most likely sub-category.
